      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "A poor start proved costly for PARIS JAMILLA (9) last time out but she had won two in a row prior, one here and the other from this row. Should enjoy a pretty soft run from this draw and the sprint lane is in play so she could bounce back. THE ITALIAN DREAM (2) impressed with a resuming win from a wide barrier here two runs ago then came from the back row for fifth at her latest appearance. Race fit and should enjoy an economical run from this draw. Leading hope. Manners can be a problem for RAKERO WARRIOR NZ (8) but a win from this row three back at Melton showed what he is capable of when on his game. OX KNOX (3) has had some tough barriers of late but should have no excuses from this advantageous draw.",
